Edward,<br>
     Saw your post after I checked to see if mine took.  I understand the need for you and others to have a place for just the vets ourselves.  This is not it.  The site was set up as a place where vet and non-vet; pro-war, anti-war and neutral alike would dialogue.  It has served that purpose well, yet not occasionally without a cost in pain, anguish or anger.  It's part of the price we pay for being human, with all the diifferences and imperfections tha entails.<br>
     As a Christian, I definately do not approve of what that insensitive bunch did at Oklahoma City.  Interfering with someone else's service is not exercising one's freedom of religion, but abrogating someone else's.  There are still too many like the old Puritans who want religious freedom only for themselves.  THat's a double standard.  Have had a brush or two with &quot;fightin' fundies&quot; myself.  Some have a rather low tolerance quotient for anything in sight that doesn't agrre with their doctrinal positions.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@ipcphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;. 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


